==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Excurrent
<hw>Ex*cur"rent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>excurrens</ets>, p. p. of excurrere, excursum, to run out;
<ets>ex</ets> out + <ets>currere</ets> to run. See
<er>Current</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Running or flowing out</def>;
as: <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Running or extending out; <as>as, an
<ex>excurrent</ex> midrib, one which projects beyond the apex of a leaf;
an <ex>excurrent</ex> steam or trunk, one which continues to the
top</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧l.)</fld> <def>Characterized by a current
which flows outward; <as>as, an <ex>excurrent</ex> orifice or
tube</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Excurse</ent>⟦br⟧
